Model - Approach 2

("LiDAR Hull" Approach)

Summary: This document contains a summary of the mixed-effects model that best fit the data for this approach (which was chosen through a model selection process and identified as the model with the lowest AIC value):

  • Section 1. Model form + output.
  • Section 2. Exploration of model fit.

Section 1

This figure shows the form of the best-fitting model, as well as a table with model output. For the random effect term in the model, 'LocalityName' is nested within 'Month'

model <- lmer(Composite_Albedo ~
                    Treatment + 
                    Productivity_Index +
                    Canopy_Height_MAD +
                    Clearcut_Lidar +
                    Moose_Density +
                    Treatment*Canopy_Height_MAD +
                    (1 | Month/LocalityName),
            data = model_data)
